Of course! Here's a JavaScript function to capitalize the first letter and lowercase the rest:

```javascript
function capitalizeFirstLetter(str) {
  if (!str) return '';
  return str.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + str.slice(1).toLowerCase();
}

// Example Usage:
console.log(`'hello world': ${capitalizeFirstLetter('hello world')}`); // "Hello world"
console.log(`'JAVASCRIPT': ${capitalizeFirstLetter('JAVASCRIPT')}`); // "Javascript"
